<br>
Simply because there is no way we (the players) can define what is a bug, what is an oversight by the devs or what was intended.<br>
<br>
That is not to say some exploits/bugs aren't blindingly obvious - the mob that stays stuck while you nuke it down - yes that is an exploit pure and simple. But someone has already brought up the example of quadding. I would add to this the use of grav flux in the Concussion quest - an exploit? Quite possibly - there have been whole threads on this subject on this boards. <br>
<br>
In my opinion the idea of an exploit is merely something they dont like. In effect it is a bug or an oversight that THEY introduced (throught lack of thinking something through, lack of testing etc.) and that they then aim to blame the players for utilising. <br>
<br>
The person above who said an exploit was any player having more intelligence that the developers had a very telling point. <br>
<br>
So at an attempt at a definition:<br>
<br>
An exploit - using to your advantage something in the code that SOE decides they do not like.<br>
<br>
 <p>Kabach Cryonax, Wizard of the 56th Flame<br>
